message.text:
In view of the inclement weather brought about by Tropical Storm “Kristine” affecting the whole country, particularly the Island of Luzon, work in government offices and classes at all levels in Luzon are hereby suspended on 23 October 2024.

However, those agencies whose functions involve the delivery of basic and health services, preparedness/response to disasters and calamities, and/or the performance of other vital services shall continue with their operations and render the necessary services.

The suspension of work for private companies and offices is left to the discretion of their respective heads.

- Office of the Executive Secretary

message.text:
In view of the inclement weather brought about by Tropical Storm “Kristine” affecting the whole country, particularly the Island of Luzon, work in government offices and classes at all levels in Luzon are hereby suspended on 23 October 2024.

However, those agencies whose functions involve the delivery of basic and health services, preparedness/response to disasters and calamities, and/or the performance of other vital services shall continue with their operations and render the necessary services.

The suspension of work for private companies and offices is left to the discretion of their respective heads.

- Office of the Executive Secretary

message.text:
In view of the inclement weather brought about by Tropical Storm “Kristine” affecting the whole country, particularly the Island of Luzon, work in government offices and classes at all levels in Luzon are hereby suspended on 23 October 2024.

However, those agencies whose functions involve the delivery of basic and health services, preparedness/response to disasters and calamities, and/or the performance of other vital services shall continue with their operations and render the necessary services.

The suspension of work for private companies and offices is left to the discretion of their respective heads.

- Office of the Executive Secretary

Suspendido na rin ang pasok ng mga kawani sa Pamahalaang Lungsod ng Maynila ngayong Miyerkules, October 23, 2024, dahil sa masamang panahon na dala ng bagyong #KristinePH . 

Ayon ito sa anunsyo ng Malacañang Palace sa pamamagitan ng Presidential Communications Office , kung saan suspendido ang trabaho sa gobyerno at klase sa mga paaralan sa buong Luzon.

Mananatiling bukas ang mga ahensiya ng pamahalaan na nagbibigay ng basic services, disaster response, at health services.

Ang suspensiyon ng pasok sa pribadong kumpanya ay nakasalalay sa desisyon ng kanilang pamunuan.

message.text:
In view of the inclement weather brought about by Tropical Storm “Kristine” affecting the whole country, particularly the Island of Luzon, work in government offices and classes at all levels in Luzon are hereby suspended on 23 October 2024.

However, those agencies whose functions involve the delivery of basic and health services, preparedness/response to disasters and calamities, and/or the performance of other vital services shall continue with their operations and render the necessary services.

The suspension of work for private companies and offices is left to the discretion of their respective heads.

- Office of the Executive Secretary
